<h1>Debian for S/390 and zSeries</h1>

<h2>Status</h2>

<p>The port to S/390 will be released with the next version of Debian
(codename woody). Almost all packages have been compiled for s390 and the
auto-builder is keeping up well with new packages. In fact, it is
keeping up better than any other port besides i386, see the
<a href="http://buildd.debian.org/stats/">buildd statistics</a> for
more information.</p>

<p>The first version of the boot-floppies that supported s390 was 3.0.14
using kernel 2.4.7. Newer boot-floppies since 3.0.18 use kernel 2.4.16
which also supports the ext3 journaling file system on s390. There is also
support for the non-free
<a href="http://www10.software.ibm.com/developerworks/opensource/linux390/">OCO
modules from IBM</a> using a second initial RAM disk but these modules are
not distributed by Debian and probably never will be.</p>

