<h2>Development</h2>

<p>The build server for the S/390 architecture is running on a VM
guest on a Multiprise 3000. The machine is hosted by <a
href="http://www.millenux.de/">Millenux</a>, the distributor of the <a
href="http://linux.s390.org/">Think Blue distribution for S/390</a>.
The machine is administrated by Gerhard Tonn.  Any Debian developer,
who is interested to help, may request an account on the build server
by sending a mail to him.</p>

<p>The wanna-build DB is on auric.debian.org. Please ask Ryan Murray
&lt;rmurray@cyberhqz.com&gt; to be added to the wb-s390 group, so that
you are authorized to work with the database.</p>

<h2>Mailing List</h2>

<p>If you would like to help, you should subscribe to the debian-s390
mailing list. To do this, send a message containing the word "subscribe"
as the subject to
<a href="mailto:debian-s390-request@lists.debian.org">\
debian-s390-request@lists.debian.org</a> to sign up, or use the 
<a href="$(HOME)/MailingLists/subscribe">\
Mailing List subscription</a> page.</p>

<p>The list is archived at <a href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-s390/">\
http://lists.debian.org/debian-s390/</a></p>.

